description: Home minister Amit Shah commends Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel for uniting 553 princely states post-Independence, forming the Union of India. Shah laments Patel's recognition delay, celebrates his legacy with PM Modi's initiatives. The 'Run for Unity' marks Patel's immense contribution to national unity.
title: Patel was 'forgotten for yrs' and 'deprived' of Bharat Ratna: Amit Shah

description: Twelve years after a special court allowed the closure of a corruption case against former Tamil Nadu chief minister O Panneerselvam, the Madras high court has reversed the decision, reviving the case and directing the transfer of all documents to a special court in Madurai.
title: After 12 years, HC orders revival of graft case against Tamil Nadu ex-CM O Panneerselvam

description: Rebels pose challenges for major alliances in Maharashtra as nominations for assembly polls close. Mahayuti identified 80 rebels, while nearly 150 candidates filed nominations against their official candidates. Both alliances say candidates for all seats are declared. Withdrawal of nominations by Nov 4 may help manage disputes and clarify the final number of contestants.
title: Close to 150 rebels in Maharashtra poll fray, pose challenge to MVA & Mahayuti

description: Police in Mumbai arrested a 20-year-old from Noida for allegedly making a hoax call about a death threat to NCP MLA Zeeshan Siddique and actor Salman Khan. The accused, facing financial difficulties, hoped for a reward for providing this false information.
title: UP man who called Siddique son about plot to kill him, Salman held

description: At a rally for his grandnephew, Sharad Pawar mimicked Ajit Pawar's emotional speech, rejecting claims that he split the family and emphasizing he never leveraged emotional appeals. Sharad also contested Ajit's accusation of family division and expressed frustration over legal battles within the NCP.
title: Didn't give Sule any post, made Ajit deputy CM four times: Sharad Pawar

description: Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah assured farmers they won't be evicted from their lands despite allegations of them being marked as Waqf properties. Notices issued during the previous BJP government are being rescinded. A task force is established to resolve errors, while BJP's Vijayendra and Union Minister Pralhad Joshi demand accountability for notices.
title: No farmer will be evicted, says Siddaramaiah after Waqf land row

description: Veteran politician Anees Ahmed missed the 3pm deadline to file his nomination for Nagpur Central by just two minutes after facing multiple obstacles, including road restrictions and last-minute documentation. This resulted in no representation for Vanchit Bahujan Aghadi and inadvertently benefited the Congress.
title: Congress veteran limps his way to file papers in Nagpur, but misses deadline by 2 mins

description: Justice Sanjiv Khanna, known for his dedication to citizen rights and judicial integrity, will become the 51st Chief Justice of India on November 11. His tenure will focus on reducing case backlog in the Supreme Court. Despite past setbacks, Khanna stands firm on maintaining privacy and dignity while prioritizing swift and fair justice delivery.
title: As CJI, Justice Khanna to focus on paring pendency

description: The District Consumer Commission in Visakhapatnam directed South Central Railway to compensate a passenger for inadequate amenities during a Tirumala Express journey. Despite booking for a comfortable ride, V Murthy and his family faced water scarcity and lack of air conditioning in the toilets, leading to a complaint and subsequent action for service deficiency.
title: Rail passenger gets Rs 25,000 in damages for waterless toilet

description: Diwali will be historic this year, said PM Narendra Modi. After 500 years, thousands of lamps will illuminate the Ayodhya temple where Ram Lalla’s idol was consecrated earlier this year. Modi announced development projects worth Rs 12,850 crore and extended Ayushman Bharat health insurance to all senior citizens aged 70 and above.
title: PM Modi: Historic Diwali in Ayodhya as Ram in temple after 500 years

description: UK's King Charles III and Queen consort Camilla made a discreet four-day visit to Bengaluru, avoiding media attention. They took a rejuvenation break at Soukya Health and Wellness Centre after attending the Commonwealth Heads of Government Meeting in Samoa. This was the king's first overseas trip since his cancer diagnosis.
title: King Charles, Queen Camilla take 4-day 'rejuvenation break' in Bengaluru

description: A 13-year-old boy in Rajasthan's Jhunjhunu district died after a homemade firecracker exploded in his pocket, critically injuring him. Himanshu, with a friend's help, mixed sulphur and potassium to create the explosive without their families' knowledge. The explosion occurred when a spark ignited the mixture in his pocket.
title: Rajasthan teen dies as cracker explodes in pocket

description: During Spanish PM Pedro Sanchez's visit to India, both nations condemned terrorism, urging action against groups such as LeT and JeM. They stressed the need for firm implementation of UNSC resolutions and praised Spain's support for terrorism victims. The leaders also reaffirmed their commitment to enhancing India-EU strategic partnerships and boosting connectivity projects.
title: India, Spain vow war on terror, seek action against LeT, JeM

description: A third-year engineering student from a private college in Coimbatore jumped off the fourth floor of his hostel, sustaining injuries to his limbs and head. Police reported that the student, A Prabhu, was suffering from severe depression and delusions of having superpowers. He is currently receiving treatment at a private hospital, with his condition being stable.
title: BTech student 'with superpower' jumps off 4th floor, suffers fractures

description: A rampant cyber scam involves criminals impersonating law enforcement officers and issuing 'Digital Arrest' threats via SMS, email, or WhatsApp. Victims are coerced into transferring large sums of money to avoid fabricated charges. Notable cases include a retired consultant losing Rs 2 crore and an elderly woman defrauded of Rs 5.9 crores. Authorities urge vigilance and reporting of suspicious activity.
title: ‘Digital arrest’: How cyber criminals use fear to loot victims

description: The induction of India's Tejas Mark-1A jets faces delays due to postponed engine supplies from General Electric, with HAL expected to deliver only 2-3 jets instead of the promised 16 by 2024-25. Ongoing negotiations for GE-F414 engines and integration issues with weapons and radar further impact the schedule.
title: Lag in US engine supply delays IAF induction of Tejas Mark-1A

description: A 69-year-old Rajasthan woman, declared 'deceased' in government records, traveled 565km to Delhi seeking to resolve her pension issue. Similar erroneous entries have cut off pensions for many in Rajasthan. Activists highlight how mandatory Aadhaar linking leads to systemic failures, impacting over 1 crore pensioners. They urge immediate rectification and accountability for officials.
title: Rajasthan's 'living dead' pensioners travel to Delhi to highlight their plight

description: In Rajasthan's Sikar district, a private bus lost control and crashed into an overbridge wall, killing at least 12 people and injuring over 41. Eyewitnesses reported the bus was racing another vehicle and failed to navigate a turn. The incident occurred on the Bikaner-Jaipur highway near Laxmangarh.
title: 12 killed, over 41 injured in Rajasthan bus accident

description: Over 150 were injured in an explosion caused by firecrackers during a Theyyam performance at a Kerala temple. Three officials have been arrested for negligence. The blast, triggered by sparks from the firecrackers igniting stored fireworks, resulted in 16 people sustaining critical injuries, with seven on ventilator support.
title: Fireworks accident at Kerala temple festival injures 154

description: The Madras High Court is set to decide on a public interest writ petition challenging Tamil Nadu Deputy Chief Minister Udhayanidhi Stalin's choice of wearing T-shirts with the DMK party's symbol. The court has asked the state to clarify if the dress code for government servants applies to ministers and whether a T-shirt is considered formal or casual attire.
title: HC notice to Tamil Nadu govt on Udhayanidhi’s attire

description: UP police dismantles a gang selling arms online through Instagram, Facebook, and WhatsApp, arresting seven individuals, including two buyers, during a weapon delivery in Muzaffarnagar. Confiscated items include country-made guns, imported pistols, bullets, a bike, and a car. Investigations reveal connections with other gangs in nearby districts.
title: Guns sold on WhatsApp, Instagram & Facebook in UP, 7 held

description: A businessman in Rani Bagh was targeted for extortion by the Bambiha syndicate, demanding Rs 10 crore. The Delhi Police apprehended two suspects involved in the shooting while the gang is operated from the US by Pawan Shokeen and Lucky Patial. The police also linked the group to pro-Khalistani factions, increasing concerns about Delhi’s underworld.
title: 2 held after Bambiha gang demanded Rs 10 crore from businessman, fired at his house

description: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) plans to approach the Supreme Court to reopen a money laundering probe against Santiago Martin, a significant political contributor. This follows a Madras High Court ruling deeming the withdrawal of a corruption case against him illegal, potentially reinstating ED's case under PMLA.
title: ED to seek SC nod to resume probe against 'lottery king'

description: Chhattisgarh High Court denied a plea for the release of a 24-year-old convicted under the Pocso Act, noting that his age at the time of the crime was irrelevant despite his progress reports showing reformation. The court upheld his transfer to an adult prison, emphasizing that leniency could lead to significant societal risks and law-and-order issues.
title: HC junks plea to release convict, now 24, held as juvenile in Pocso case

description: Following a dispute over the presentation of a report by Delhi Waqf Board, the Joint Parliamentary Committee on Waqf Amendment Bill, 2024, agrees to hear Delhi government’s representative next month. Opposition members protested the appointment of non-Muslim Ashwini Kumar as Waqf Board administrator and disputed the report’s content.
title: After opposition protest, Waqf JPC to hear Delhi govt representative

description: An Instagram user shares a viral video showcasing Amazon Alexa's ability to remotely launch rockets and firecrackers using voice commands.
title: Amazon Alexa ‘bursting’ crackers with Happy Diwali message. Watch

description: J&K Police dismantled a heroin smuggling ring in Baramulla, arresting three individuals and seizing 2.7kg heroin valued at Rs 20 crore. Nazim Din, Waqar Ahmad Khawaja, and Manzoor Ahmad Bhat were detained following coordinated busts, with further investigations ongoing to identify additional members of the network.
title: Heroin smuggling network busted in Baramulla, 3 held

description: Security forces eliminated two more terrorists after an attack near Akhnoor in Jammu, resulting in the death of military dog Phantom. The operation, involving special forces and advanced equipment, concluded with the deaths of all three terrorists. Increased surveillance aims to counter heightened infiltration attempts in the region as winter approaches.
title: Army ambulance attack in J&K: All 3 terrorists killed

description: If Donald Trump is re-elected, Harry or Meghan must not have any fear of being deported, Eric said. "Truthfully I don't give a damn about Prince Harry and I don't think this country does either," Eric said. Prince Harry ran into trouble after it was found out that he might have lied about his drug abuse when he applied for his US visa. In his memoir, Prince Harry admitted to having taken drugs which should have got his visa application in the US rejected.
title: Donald Trump's son says no one in America cares about Harry or his 'unpopular wife'

description: Chaos erupted in a Ghaziabad courtroom as lawyers demanded their case be heard immediately, leading to a police lathicharge when they refused to leave. The protest escalated to vandalism, with furniture set ablaze and cameras damaged. The incident stemmed from a land dispute involving lawyer Nahar Singh Yadav.
title: Cops lathicharge lawyers amid chaos in Ghaziabad court

description: At least five workers were killed and two injured in a terrorist attack on the site of a dam under construction in Panjgur, Balochistan. The attackers arrived on motorcycles, opened fire, and set machinery ablaze before escaping. The incident underscores the ongoing violence affecting development projects in the region.
title: Terrorists kill 5 dam workers in Balochistan

description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for October 30, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope today, October 30: Read your today's astrological predictions

description: A methamphetamine lab in Greater Noida, linked to the Mexican CJNG cartel, was busted by NCB, seizing 95kg of drugs. A West Delhi businessman, a Tihar jail warden, and a Mumbai chemist were involved. Chemicals and machinery were recovered, and four suspects were arrested.
title: Meth lab linked to Mexican cartel busted in Greater Noida

description: The Election Commission refutes Congress' allegations of compromised electoral processes and EVM misuse in Haryana polls. It asserts that no evidence of wrongdoing exists, chastises Congress for creating doubts, and emphasises that such claims can incite public unrest. The detailed response clarifies misunderstandings regarding EVM battery status and counting procedures.
title: ‘Frivolous doubts’: EC hits out at Congress on Haryana EVMs

description: PM Modi criticizes AAP and TMC for not implementing Ayushman Bharat in Delhi and Bengal, highlighting their political interests over public health. He apologized to elderly residents who cannot benefit from the scheme and emphasized the expansion of healthcare infrastructure, including the inauguration of various health projects and the launch of the U-WIN portal.
title: PM Modi slams AAP, TMC for not rolling out Ayushman cover

description: JPMorgan Chase has filed lawsuits against customers accused of exploiting a viral 'infinite money glitch' to withdraw over $661,000 fraudulently from ATMs. The scheme went viral on TikTok in late August, leading to large cash withdrawals before the bank closed the loophole. Chase is now pursuing the stolen funds and cooperating with law enforcement.
title: JPMorgan is suing customers who stole thousands of dollars in ‘infinite money ATM glitch’

description: Choti Diwali, celebrated a day before Diwali, symbolizes the victory of good over evil and marks the occasion with rituals like lighting diyas and cleaning homes. The day fosters unity, positivity, and spiritual renewal, offering heartfelt exchanges of wishes. It prepares participants for the main festival, underscoring values like compassion, love, and togetherness.
title: Choti Diwali: Wishes, messages, images, quotes and greetings

description: ​It was widely reported that Elon Musk had a tryst with Nicole Shanahan which led her then-husband, Google co-founder Sergey Brin, to file for divorce. Shanahan denied the affair but admitted to having sex with Elon. The NYT report said during that time Elon Musk wanted to have a baby with Shanahan through IVF and offered to donate sperm but she refused.
title: Elon Musk offered to donate sperm to a married couple: Report

description: The Kansas City Chiefs are reinforcing their roster ahead of the NFL trade deadline on November 5th, acquiring linebacker Josh Uche from the Patriots. Despite placing tight end Jody Fortson on Injured Reserve, the team remains strong with Travis Kelce's rejuvenated performance. Fans are abuzz with theories linking Kelce's success to Taylor Swift's charm.
title: After Travis Kelce’s first touchdown, Andy Reid's Chiefs face challenge

description: External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar stressed the need for adapting to changing geopolitical situations and advocated for a whole-of-government approach in national security at the Army Commanders' Conference 2024. The conference coincided with the final stages of troop disengagement in eastern Ladakh between India and China.
title: 'Be prepared': EAM urges military leaders to learn from global conflicts
Odisha: Pregnant govt employee in labour denied leave, loses baby
Rift in Mahayuti as Ajit Pawar snubs BJP over Nawab Malik

description: Hezbollah has elected Sheikh Naim Qassem as its new head following Hasan Nasrallah's death in an Israeli attack. Qassem, a long-time leader within the group, emphasized resilience against Israel despite recent blows. Notably, he supported a ceasefire initiative by parliamentary speaker Nabih Berri, marking a shift in Hezbollah's stance on conflict de-escalation.
title: Who is Naim Qassem, Hezbollah's new chief

description: Manchester City manager Pep Guardiola has praised both Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo, labelling Ronaldo a 'monster' created by Messi. Guardiola's comments follow the 2024 Ballon d'Or, where City's Rodri ended the Messi-Ronaldo dominance. Rodri's win is a significant moment for Spanish football, echoing Guardiola's belief that Spanish footballers deserved global recognition.
title: 'Ronaldo was a monster and the father of that monster is…': Guardiola
Bengal doctor held for raping patient after injecting sedatives

description: Nearly 1,100 Indian nationals living illegally in the US were repatriated during the 2023-24 financial year. The US department of homeland security noted over 160,000 removals and 495 international repatriation flights, highlighting collaboration with foreign governments to address irregular migration and disrupt criminal networks.
title: US deported over 1,000 illegal Indian immigrants in a year

description: Smriti Mandhana on Tuesday surpassed Mithali Raj to become the Indian player with the most ODI centuries, scoring her eighth century in a match against New Zealand at the Narendra Modi Stadium. Mandhana’s 100 off 122 balls helped India secure a six-wicket victory, clinching the series 2-1. Mithali  held the previous record with seven centuries.
title: Smriti slams 8th ODI ton, surpasses Mithali to become...
Hoax bomb threat menace continues, over 100 flights affected

description: Comedian Tony Hinchcliffe sparked backlash with a derogatory comment about Puerto Rico during a rally for Donald Trump in New York. This has caused significant political fallout, particularly in the swing state of Pennsylvania, which has a large Puerto Rican population. The incident may impact Trump's chances in key states, highlighting the sensitivity of Latino voter support.
title: How a comedian's 'garbage' remark could cost Trump US presidential polls

description: Ciara celebrated a significant career milestone by receiving a plaque from SiriusXM and Pandora for achieving over 3 billion streams, with hits like 'Goodies' and 'Level Up' contributing heavily. Meanwhile, her husband Russell Wilson led the Pittsburgh Steelers to their 22nd consecutive MNF victory against the Giants, setting a new NFL record.
title: Ciara celebrates 'Billionaire' milestone in music

description: Instagram's direct messaging feature is facing global disruptions, particularly affecting users in India, the US, and the UK. Downdetector reports peak complaints in India around 6 pm, while users have also voiced issues on Twitter. Despite the widespread outage, the Times of India Tech team did not encounter any problems exchanging messages on Instagram.
title: Instagram DM outage: Countries hit and how users reacted on social media

description: Tony de Zorzi scored his maiden Test century to help South Africa dominate the first day of the second Test against Bangladesh, ending at 307/2. De Zorzi's century came with a crucial 201-run partnership with Tristan Stubbs, who scored 106. South Africa's strong position sets them up for a possible series-clinching win.
title: Watch: De Zorzi celebrates maiden Test ton with iconic move

description: Donald Trump, at a Monday rally, fiercely rebuffed allegations of being a Nazi, amid backlash from a previous rally laced with extremist rhetoric and offensive remarks against Kamala Harris and minorities. The controversial events have intensified Latino voters' scrutiny and heightened tensions as the election approaches.
title: Trump says he's 'opposite of a Nazi' as toxic MSG rally poisons America

description: From Ishaan Khatter's increasing public appearances with Chandni Bainz to Vidya Balan's openness to starring in Dirty Picture 2, the entertainment world is abuzz. Salman Khan faces new death threats, while Hrithik Roshan and Amitabh Bachchan share updates on their respective projects and memories.
title: Top 5 entertainment news of the day

description: Former Australia captain Tim Paine believes Australia are clear favourites for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy, citing India's recent struggles with form and injuries. Paine highlights the absence of Mohammed Shami and concerns over Jasprit Bumrah's workload. Australia's home advantage and stability are mentioned as key factors for their potential success against India in the upcoming series.
title: 'Australia's batting not amazing but…': Paine ahead of India Tests

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi highlights the significance of this year's Diwali as the first to celebrate Lord Ram at the newly constructed Shri Ram Janmabhoomi temple in Ayodhya. He also praises the Rozgar Mela providing jobs to 51,000 youth and Haryana's efforts in youth employment.
title: 'After 500 years': Why PM Modi has termed this Diwali 'special'

description: The Aam Aadmi Party criticizes the Ayushman Bharat scheme, calling it impractical and a scam. The party claims Delhi residents won't benefit from the scheme if implemented. PM Modi had earlier apologized to the elderly in Delhi and Bengal, as they won't receive benefits due to state governments' decisions.
title: 'Not for Delhiites': AAP on PM Modi's Ayushman Bharat attack

description: The Election Commission of India (ECI) has firmly denied Congress allegations about election irregularities in Haryana. The ECI stated that the electoral process was conducted meticulously under the observation of Congress agents, emphasizing the baseless nature of the claims. The commission is committed to protecting the integrity of the electoral process.
title: 'Pattern of raising unfounded doubts': EC sternly rebuts Cong's Haryana poll allegations

description: The US is finalising regulations to restrict investments in Chinese tech sectors such as AI, semiconductors, and quantum computing, citing national security risks. The rules, effective January 2, target advancements in military and intelligence capabilities to prevent American expertise from aiding China's technological progress.
title: US has stricter rules on AI investments in China, to go into effect on this date

description: Jaya Kishori, spiritual speaker, faced backlash for carrying a Dior bag worth over Rs 2 lakh, leading to questions about her teachings on simplicity. Kishori defended herself, stating the bag is customized and leather-free. Critics pointed out contradictions, noting her other luxurious items like a Rolex watch, which raised doubts about her message of non-materialism.
title: Jaya Kishori responds to criticism over luxury bag: 'I'm not a saint'

description: Apple is releasing AI features in iOS 18.1, iPadOS 18.1, and macOS Sequoia 15.1, offering intelligent writing tools, enhanced photo editing, and a revamped Siri. Key updates include Memory Movies in the Photos app, improved photo search, AI-powered call recording, and a new 'Reduce Interruptions' Focus mode. These features will be available on eligible devices initially in the US.
title: 7 ‘biggest’ Apple Intelligence features for iPhones, iPads and Macs
Gold prices climb to Rs 81,400 on Dhanteras demand, silver rises amid festive rush

description: Security forces neutralised three heavily armed terrorists in Jammu and Kashmir's Akhnoor, utilising AI and unmanned vehicle for a successful operation. Major General Sameer Srivastava highlighted the terrorists' significant intentions. The operation also saw the loss of an Army sniffer dog, Phantom, who saved many lives. Coordination with local authorities remains ongoing.
title: AI, unmanned vehicles: How Army hunted down terrorists who attacked convoy in J&K

description: Vidya Balan, a versatile Bollywood actress, revealed her struggles with weight gain due to chronic inflammation. This condition disrupts insulin and leptin functions, leading to fat accumulation. Inflammation may arise from poor diet, stress, and pollutants. Vidya’s experience emphasizes focusing on reducing inflammation through diet and lifestyle changes rather than just exercise.
title: Vidya Balan shares how inflammation made her gain weight everytime

description: Pakistan cricket is experiencing turbulence with coaching changes and leadership shifts before important tours. Former captain Babar Azam arrived in Australia and was warmly welcomed by fans. He will play in the white-ball series against Australia. Meanwhile, Gary Kirsten resigned as white-ball coach, leaving Jason Gillespie to guide the team in Australia.
title: Watch: Babar clicks selfies with fans as Pakistan reach Australia

description: A 19-year-old BTech student from Karpagam College of Engineering in Coimbatore believed he had superpowers and jumped off the fourth floor of his hostel. He sustained severe fractures and head injuries. The student was first given aid at a local hospital and then transferred to Ganga Hospital for further treatment.
title: 'Believes he has superpowers': Coimbatore student jumps from fourth floor

description: Jharkhand CM Hemant Soren accused BJP of fostering societal divisions and neglecting marginalized communities. This followed Assam CM Himanta Biswa Sarma's comments alleging Bangladeshi infiltration in Jharkhand. Soren criticized the central government for poor border security and highlighted his administration's support for underprivileged groups. BJP leaders claimed rising Muslim population due to infiltration and promised anti-immigrant measures.
title: 'These people stir up Hindu-Muslim tensions': Hemant Soren on Himanta

description: Congress President Mallikarjun Kharge accuses PM Narendra Modi of protecting Sebi chairperson Madhabi Puri Buch amid malpractice allegations, claiming Modi jeopardizes small investors' financial security and engineered a monopoly for Adani. Kharge and Congress leaders demand a Joint Parliamentary Committee probe into Sebi's integrity under Buch's leadership.
title: Congress alleges PM Modi ‘shielding’ chairperson Madhabi Buch

description: Basit Ali criticized Gary Kirsten's sudden exit as Pakistan's limited-overs coach, expressing concern over Pakistan cricket's decline. He compared the situation to other countries' approaches and mocked Kirsten’s selection preferences. Kirsten's resignation followed internal tensions with the PCB. Jason Gillespie will replace Kirsten for the upcoming white-ball tour of Australia.
title: 'Mazak bana diya hai Pakistan ka': Basit Ali

description: Following a confrontation during a Joint Parliamentary Committee meeting on the Waqf Bill, TMC MP Kalyan Banerjee defended his actions against BJP's Abhijit Gangopadhyay. Banerjee clashed with Gangopadhyay, leading to him hurling a glass bottle that injured him and Chairman Jagdambika Pal. Banerjee was suspended for a day for his conduct.
title: 'He abused me': TMC MP Kalyan Banerjee defends smashing bottle at Waqf JPC meet

description: Kolkata Knight Riders (KKR) have finally initiated talks with captain Shreyas Iyer regarding his retention plans just days before the IPL deadline. Despite being approached by multiple franchises for a leadership role, there has been no clear decision on Iyer’s future with KKR yet. The franchise, considering several retentions, is also looking at potential fresh additions to the team setup.
title: Talks on between Shreyas Iyer and KKR as IPL retention deadline nears

description: A 20-year-old from Noida, Gufran Khan, was arrested for making a veiled threat regarding MLA Zeeshan Siddique and actor Salman Khan's safety through a WhatsApp message and phone call. Khan's intention was to solicit money by providing information about alleged threats, which turned out to be false.
title: Zeeshan Siddique, Salman Khan get threat message; accused arrested from Noida

description: Swiggy Instamart has rolled out a 'Shopping List' feature on its quick commerce platform, influenced by a suggestion from a Gurgaon entrepreneur on X (formerly Twitter).
title: Swiggy Instamart founder thanks Gurgaon entrepreneur for this feature

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi inaugurated health projects worth Rs 12,850 crore, enhancing nationwide healthcare infrastructure with initiatives like Ayushman Bharat expansion for senior citizens, advanced AIIMS and ESIC facilities, new medical colleges in Madhya Pradesh, drone-based healthcare, the U-WIN portal for vaccinations, and a health awareness campaign.
title: PM Modi unveils Rs 12,850 crore health projects

description: A western-style toilet in a 2nd class Indian train is criticized for its poor condition by travel blogger Irina Moreno. Her viral Instagram video sparked mixed reactions; some reasoned low ticket prices justify the state, while others insisted on basic cleanliness for all passengers. The video accrued over 5.8 million views.
title: Video of poor train toilet conditions by foreign blogger stirs debate

description: Shrinivas Vanga, a legislator from Shiv Sena (Shinde) in Palghar, went missing after losing his ticket for the 2024 elections to Rajendra Gavit. Vanga, who expressed regret for leaving Uddhav Balasaheb Thackeray, was last seen leaving his home with a bag. Heavy police presence and searches are underway to locate him.
title: Palghar MLA Srinivas Vanga goes missing after being denied ticket

description: Lawyers in Ghaziabad court were injured after police used lathis to disperse them following a disruption during a hearing. The lawyers demanded the judge hear their case immediately, causing a disturbance. The incident led to 8-10 lawyers getting injured, prompting calls for a strike and action against the judge.
title: Police lathi-charge on lawyers in Ghaziabad court

description: Brazil, under President Lula da Silva, has chosen not to join China's Belt and Road Initiative but will seek other ways to collaborate with Chinese investors. Brazil aims to align its infrastructure projects with investment funds tied to BRI without officially joining, citing concerns about immediate benefits and potential U.S. relations under a Trump administration.
title: Setback for China's BRI as Brazil follows India's lead, rejects initiative

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi criticized the Bengal and Delhi governments for not implementing the Ayushman Bharat scheme, thereby denying elderly citizens in these regions access to the extended benefits. The scheme, now covering all citizens aged 70 and above, provides free hospital treatment and an 'Ayushman Vaya Vandana' card.
title: Why PM Modi apologised to the elderly in Delhi, Bengal

description: Matthew Hayden, celebrating his 53rd birthday, predicts an Australian victory in the upcoming Border Gavaskar Trophy but expects a tough contest from Rohit Sharma-led India. He argues that drop-in pitches in three of the five venues reduce Australia's home advantage.  Stadiums in Perth, Adelaide and Melbourne use drop-in pitches.
title: 'Australia will win, but watch Team India go!' - Hayden on BGT

description: A violent clash erupted between CPI and BJP workers at Veerarkavu Temple after a fireworks explosion injured over 150 people during a festival in Kasargod, with ten sustaining severe burns. The District Collector cited lack of safety measures, as fireworks storage and bursting sites were too close, and no permissions were secured for the storage.
title: Kerala fire: Clash erupts between BJP-CPM workers in Kasargod, watch video
Breaking Bad in Noida?: NCB busts meth lab, seizes 95kg drugs; Tihar warden arrested

description: Kunal Kamra accepts Bhavish Aggarwal’s offer to work with Ola after getting tagged in numerous posts related to service issues. Kamra also highlights essential action points for Ola Electric.
title: Kunal Kamra ‘accepts’ Ola CEO Bhavish Aggarwal’s “Aaja Service Centre” offer

description: At a Michigan rally, Kamala Harris faced an awkward moment when her request for attendees to shout their own names was met with silence. The event, attended by college students in Ann Arbor, also saw interruptions by pro-Palestinian protesters. Harris continued focusing on unity and voter engagement for the upcoming elections.
title: Watch: Awkward silence after Harris tells crowd to shout their own names

description: Priyanka Gandhi Vadra praised the voters in Wayanad for their unwavering support for Rahul Gandhi amidst a campaign against him. She highlighted their early recognition of his qualities and fight. Priyanka recently stepped into electoral politics and signed nomination papers for the upcoming Lok Sabha bypoll in Wayanad.
title: 'Massive campaign against my brother': Priyanka thanks Wayanad for 'recognising' Rahul

description: Ishan Kishan, who has been away from the Indian cricket team for 11 months, has made a strong comeback through consistent domestic performances. Rejuvenated by a training stint with Hardik Pandya for Baroda, Kishan's hunger for the game has returned and he's eager to seize opportunities with the India A squad.
title: Ishan Kishan: 'Hungry to get an international match'

description: Union home minister Amit Shah emphasized Sardar Patel's delayed recognition with the Bharat Ratna and attempts to undermine his legacy. Shah lauded Patel's role in India's unification and highlighted the government's efforts to honor him, including the installation of his statue and preparations for his 150th birth anniversary celebrations.
title: Sardar Patel deprived of Bharat Ratna for too long: Amit Shah

description: A 67-year-old woman from Mumbai was scammed out of Rs 14 lakh by fraudsters posing as Delhi Telecom and Cyber Crime officials. They convinced her that she was involved in a money laundering case and persuaded her to transfer her savings for verification. The woman realized the fraud after consulting with her son and reported it to the police.
title: 'Digital arrest': Senior citizen duped in Mumbai, forced to pay Rs 14 lakh

description: 10-year-old spiritual influencer Abhinav Arora received life threats from Lawrence Bishnoi's gang. Famous for his spiritual content, Abhinav faced backlash for dancing during a religious procession. He has over 950,000 followers on Instagram and is recognized as India’s Youngest Spiritual Orator by Union minister Nitin Gadkari.
title: Who is Abhinav Arora? 10-year-old influencer juggling spiritual fame

description: In the 2020-21 Border-Gavaskar Trophy series, Tim Paine defended sledging Ravichandran Ashwin, stating Ashwin often got him out, which frustrated him. Despite this, India won the series 2-1. Ashwin, along with Hanuma Vihari, secured a draw in the Sydney Test, after which he missed the Brisbane Test due to a back spasm.
title: Why Paine doesn't regret sledging Ashwin in 2020-21 Sydney Test

description: Daylight Saving Time (DST) will end on November 3, 2024, in North America and ended on October 27, 2024, in Europe. The U.S. Senate voted to make DST permanent in 2022, but the proposal stalled. The shift back to standard time results in darker evenings and can affect health and sleep patterns. Below are a few of the tips which one can follow for better well-being.
title: Daylight saving time ending soon: How it affects your health and tips to prepare

description: Salman Khan has received another death threat following the murder of his friend Baba Siddique by the Lawrence Bishnoi gang. A 20-year-old from Noida, Gulfan Khan, was arrested for the threat. Baba's son, Zeeshan, revealed Salman has been deeply worried since the incident, raising safety concerns for both.
title: Salman Khan receives new death threat; suspect arrested in Noida

description: World Stroke Day on October 29 emphasizes the importance of stroke prevention, treatment, and care. Using acronyms like FAST and BE FAST helps identify symptoms quickly. Prompt treatment within the Golden Hour is crucial to reducing brain damage and increasing recovery chances. Public awareness encourages healthy habits and understanding of risk factors for better outcomes.
title: World Stroke Day: Understanding Golden Hour and its importance

description: In 2013, Bollywood icons Salman Khan and Shah Rukh Khan ended their feud at Baba Siddique's Iftar party, after a fallout dating back to 2008. Siddique, who passed away in October 2024, orchestrated the reconciliation, resulting in a heartfelt hug that moved fans and symbolized the mending of their relationship. Baba Siddique downplayed his role in this emotional moment.
title: Throwback to PIC of Salman Khan, Baba Siddique, and Shah Rukh Khan hugging

description: iOS 18.1 introduces Apple Intelligence, a personal intelligence system that enhances productivity with AI-powered tools. Key features include advanced writing tools, a redesigned Siri with improved language understanding, and a smarter Photos app with intelligent search and editing capabilities. The update is available for specific iPhone models.
title: Apple Intelligence comes with iOS 18.1: Eligible iPhones, how to download

description: Gold buying on Dhanteras 2024: Despite a 30% price surge since last Dhanteras, experts recommend investing in gold this year, anticipating further gains due to global economic factors. Options include physical gold, ETFs, and digital gold, though caution is advised for short-term investments.
title: Dhanteras 2024: Should you buy gold today?

description: MS Dhoni recalls the challenge of playing the final day in drawn Test matches, feeling it was exhausting and monotonous. At a promotional event, he expressed his preference for the current, more result-oriented Test matches. Dhoni retired in 2014 as India's most successful Test captain, noted for his calm leadership and strategic acumen.
title: Dhoni: 'For me, the most difficult time in a Test match was...'

description: India's home record decline has sparked concerns over the careers of cricket legends Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli. With both players showing declining performances, especially in Test cricket, fans hope they can redeem themselves in the upcoming Test against New Zealand before a crucial Test series in Australia. Their future in Test cricket hangs in the balance.
title: Is it the end of the road for Virat Kohli and Rohit Sharma?

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi distributed over 51,000 appointment letters to youth nationwide under the Rozgar Mela initiative, emphasizing the government's focus on job creation. The event, held at 40 locations, included foundational training for new recruits via the 'Karmayogi Prarambh' module to enhance skills.
title: PM Modi distributes over 51,000 appointment letters under Rozgar Mela

description: BJP spokesperson Jaiveer Shergill shared a delightful video of his father dancing at Diljit Dosanjh’s concert in Delhi, which charmed the internet. Diljit, who recently returned to India, launched his Dil-Luminati Tour at Jawaharlal Nehru Stadium, creating an electrifying atmosphere by waving the Indian flag.
title: BJP spokesperson Jaiveer Shergill’s dad grooves at Diljit Dosanjh concert

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi praised Rani Rampal, former India women's hockey captain, for her 16-year career and contributions to the sport. Rani, who scored 205 goals in 254 matches, retires as one of India's most decorated players and will now mentor sub-junior players. Modi highlighted her remarkable performance at the Tokyo 2021 Olympics.
title: 'Your No. 28 jersey was ... ': PM Modi to ex-hockey captain Rani Rampal

description: Gary Kirsten resigned as Pakistan's limited-overs coach due to dissatisfaction with the restructuring of coaching roles by the PCB, which has removed head coaches from the selection committee. Kirsten's resignation follows Pakistan's recent loss to England in the first Test and early exit from the T20 World Cup.
title: 'People, media were trolling Kirsten': Ex-Pakistan cricketer

description: MS Dhoni discusses the importance of adapting cricket tactics to the strengths of players, citing England's aggressive 'Bazball' approach. He emphasizes the need for time and patience when implementing new strategies, as players require adjustment periods to adapt effectively to changes in gameplay.
title: MS Dhoni gives a masterclass on tactics like 'Bazball'

description: Former South African cricketer Gary Kirsten was unhappy with Mohammad Rizwan's appointment as Pakistan's white-ball captain, preferring another player. Following this decision, Kirsten resigned as T20I and ODI coach, and Jason Gillespie was appointed as head coach for all formats. Rizwan will lead the team against Australia and Zimbabwe. The Pakistan cricket team has undergone notable transitions lately.
title: 'Gary Kirsten wanted ... ': Ex-Pakistan cricketer drops bombshell

description: Nineteen-year-old S Hamsa Gowda spent 22 hours in chest-high water after falling into a crevice in Mydala lake channel. Despite the darkness and gushing waters, she stayed confident, standing against a rocky wall until rescuers located her. Hamsa is recovering in the hospital, treated for multiple bruises sustained during the ordeal.
title: 'I didn’t even blink': Bengaluru teen rescued after 22-hour ordeal in dark waters

description: The 2001 Australia tour of India is renowned for India's historic comeback, spearheaded by VVS Laxman and Rahul Dravid, securing a 2-1 series win. Three years on, the 2004 series saw Australia, despite Ricky Ponting's injury, clinch their first series in India in 35 years, led by stand-in captain Adam Gilchrist, with key contributions from Jason Gillespie and Shane Warne.
title: 'Was mentally scarred from the 2001 India tour': Gilchrist

description: This Dhanteras, quick commerce platforms like Blinkit, BigBasket, and Swiggy Instamart are offering 10-minute delivery of gold and silver coins. Partnering with jewelers such as Tanishq, Malabar Gold & Diamonds, and Joyalukkas, these platforms provide a convenient last-minute option. Users can purchase various denominations and types of coins using the apps.
title: Dhanteras 2024: Blinkit, Swiggy Instamart delivering gold coins in 10 mins

description: Delhi's air quality showed slight improvement but remains in the 'Poor' range with an AQI of 261. On Monday, the city recorded its sixth 'very poor' day of the month, with AQI improving from 356 to 304. Forecasts predict the air quality will deteriorate to 'very poor' or 'severe' by Diwali due to firecrackers and stubble burning.
title: Delhi AQI: At 261, city's air quality improves slightly amid festive season

description: Matthew Wade, the Australian wicketkeeper and 2021 T20 World Cup winner, announced his retirement from international cricket. Known for his sledging skills on the field, Wade played 36 Tests and 189 limited-overs matches. He is set to join Australia's coaching staff for the upcoming T20 series against Pakistan.
title: 'Not Dhoni': When Wade 'sledged himself' to leave Dhawan smiling

description: The Indian Army eliminated a second terrorist during a counter-terror operation in Jammu's Akhnoor sector following an attack on an Army convoy near the Assan temple. The operation, which involved BMP-2 infantry combat vehicles, started on Monday. The area, close to the Pakistan border, remains on high alert as searches for remaining militants continue.
title: J&K: Second terrorist killed in Akhnoor gunfight as operation continues

description: Abhinav Arora's family claims they received a death threat from Lawrence Bishnoi's gang. This follows a viral video where Abhinav is scolded by Swami Rambhadracharya. His mother dismisses the issue, viewing the scolding as a blessing, and Abhinav emphasizes the threats they're facing.
title: 10-year-old orator Abhinav Arora receives life threat from Bishnoi gang

description: Independent MP from Purnia, Pappu Yadav, alleges receiving a death threat from the Lawrence Bishnoi gang after calling them 'petty thugs.' The threat, purportedly from gangster Aman Sahu, relates to Yadav's support for Salman Khan. Yadav seeks upgraded security from Union Home Minister Amit Shah.
title: After calling Bishnoi gang ‘pettythugs’, Bihar MP Pappu Yadav gets death threats

description: A Calcutta High Court bench debates the religious need for animal sacrifices at a South Dinajpur temple, where 10,000 animals are killed annually. The court cites Section 28 of the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals Act and refers the case to the Chief Justice's bench without interim relief.
title: Veg, non-veg ‘controversy’ in Calcutta high court animal sacrifice hearing

description: Former Pakistan captain Babar Azam has been recalled for the white-ball tour of Australia after being dropped for the final two Tests against England due to inconsistent form. Experts believe he is on the verge of rediscovering his batting prowess, reminiscent of Vivian Richards, with upcoming crucial series in Australia and Zimbabwe.
title: 'Babar Azam ko dikhana hai ke woh Viv Richards hain'

description: Dhanteras, celebrated on October 29, 2024, marks the first day of Diwali. It honors Goddess Lakshmi and Lord Dhanvantari, symbols of wealth and health. People observe the festival by purchasing gold, silver, and utensils, lighting lamps, and performing pujas to attract prosperity and good fortune.
title: Dhanteras 2024: Date, city wise puja muhurat in India, puja vidhi and more

description: KL Rahul's poor form has raised questions about his place in the Indian cricket team, but the BCCI continues to back him, citing his potential and technical prowess. Ramiz Raja supports this decision, comparing it to persistence with other big-match players like Virat Kohli, and believes Rahul is just one or two innings away from regaining form.
title: 'Jab KL Rahul khelenge to sab gile shikve nikal denge'

description: Dhanteras, a key pre-Diwali celebration, will be observed on October 29, 2024. Dedicated to goddess Lakshmi and Lord Dhanvantari, it symbolizes prosperity and well-being. Traditions include buying gold, silver, and household items to attract fortune. Houses are adorned with rangolis and flowers, and specific timings are observed for rituals and puja.
title: 75+ happy Dhanteras messages, greetings, wishes and quotes to bring in good luck

description: Reddit CEO Steve Huffman aims to challenge Google's search dominance by leveraging Reddit’s specialised communities and user-generated content. Huffman notes that users are increasingly using Google to find Reddit-specific information for diverse perspectives and authentic advice. Google aids this trend by prioritising user-generated content in its search results, citing user preference for peer-based insights.
title: Reddit CEO Steve Huffman on how the company may challenge Google

description: A knife attack near a primary school in Beijing injured five people, including three children. The suspect, a 50-year-old man, is in custody. Recent incidents in Shenzhen and Shanghai highlight a worrying trend of knife violence in China, often involving school children and foreign nationals.
title: Knife attack near Beijing school leaves five injured, including 3 children

description: A major security lapse occurred in Thiruvananthapuram when five escort vehicles and the Chief Minister's official vehicle were involved in a pile-up due to a sudden brake to avoid a two-wheeler. No injuries were reported, but the police have launched an investigation into the traffic violations that led to the incident.
title: What caused the major pile-up in Kerala CM Pinarayi Vijayan's convoy?

description: Rodri won the 2024 Ballon d'Or, beating Vinicius Jr. and Jude Bellingham. Aitana Bonmati secured the women's title. Other notable awards include Carlo Ancelotti and Emma Hayes as best coaches, Kylian Mbappe and Harry Kane for top scorer, and Lamine Yamal as best young player. A look at the complete list of winners.
title: Ballon d'Or 2024 ceremony: Who won what

description: President Joe Biden celebrated Diwali at the White House with over 600 Indian Americans, highlighting the festival's significance and the contributions of the South Asian American community. Biden emphasized the importance of diversity, acknowledging America's complex journey towards unity and praising the community's enrichment of American life. Notable figures like US Surgeon General Vivek Murthy also participated.
title: 'Diwali now celebrated openly and proudly': Biden lights a diya at White House

description: Nasa astronaut Sunita Williams extended Diwali wishes from the International Space Station, highlighting the festival's message of hope and renewal. She expressed gratitude to President Joe Biden and Vice President Kamala Harris for celebrating Diwali with the Indian American community. Williams, aboard the ISS since June, will continue her mission until February next year.
title: Watch: Indian-origin astronaut Sunita Williams wishes Diwali from space

description: India's WTC final qualification becomes tougher after a series defeat against New Zealand, narrowing their lead over Australia. With six tests remaining, including a challenging series in Australia, they need minimum three wins from five Australia tests. All top five teams remain closely contested in the WTC standings. Australia will play the most Tests among the teams that have a chance of qualifying for the final.
title: World Test Championships: Team India battling for Lord's spot
Over 150 injured in fireworks accident at Kerala temple festival

description: Meta Platforms is set to launch its own AI-powered search engine to compete with Google and Bing, leveraging its Meta AI chatbot for real-time queries. This move highlights the company's strategy to reduce dependence on external search providers and the importance of ethical data usage.
title: Meta may be planning to cut its 'search ties' with Google and Microsoft

description: Microsoft accuses Google of initiating a covert smear campaign to discredit its Azure cloud business by forming a lobbying group and funding commentators. This follows Google's antitrust complaint against Microsoft, as both companies engage in escalating competitive and regulatory battles.
title: Microsoft exec writes 'open letter' against Google, claims attacking company

description: Rajasthan BJP government recalls four school textbooks a month after distribution due to technical deficiencies. One controversial chapter revisits the 2002 Godhra incident, disputing the terrorist conspiracy theory. State Congress criticizes education minister for spreading hatred and wasting public funds.
title: Rajasthan recalls text on Godhra for ‘quality checks’

description: Delhi recorded its 6th 'very poor' air day this month with an AQI of 304, which later improved marginally to 299 as winds picked up. However, air quality is expected to remain 'very poor' and may turn 'severe' on Diwali due to firecracker emissions and stubble burning.
title: Air still ‘very poor’, may be ‘severe’ on Diwali

description: Manchester City's Rodri wins the Ballon d'Or, becoming the first defensive midfielder to do so since 1990. Key in City's Premier League success and Spain's Euro victory, his win highlights the midfielder's crucial role. Rodri also emphasizes his award as a recognition for Spanish football and midfielders. Notably, neither Messi nor Ronaldo were nominated.
title: Spain's Rodri wins Ballon d'Or for best player in the world

description: Ajit Pawar, supported by a massive rally, and Yugendra Pawar, choosing a low-key ancestral visit, filed their nominations for the Baramati seat. Ajit criticized the rival faction for nominating his nephew, highlighting this as a family split. Issues like unemployment and agrarian crisis were emphasized.
title: Ajit files nomination from Baramati, terms nephew against him ‘same mistake I did’

description: A visually challenged elderly couple in Nagole, Hyderabad, lived with their deceased son's body for four days, unaware of his death. Neighbors alerted the police about a foul smell, leading to the discovery. The couple was severely malnourished and in poor condition, requiring immediate assistance.
title: Man dies, blind parents unaware of his body at home for four days in Telangana

description: Bharti Airtel reported a 168% increase in second-quarter earnings driven by higher tariffs, reaching a net profit of Rs 3,593 crore. The company also outlined a leadership transition plan effective January 2026, with COO Shashwat Sharma set to take over as CEO and MD.
title: Airtel Q2 profit surges 168% on higher tariffs

description: Authorities are investigating early morning fires that destroyed ballots in drop boxes in Portland, Oregon, and Vancouver, Washington. In Portland, only three ballots were damaged due to a fire suppressant. However, hundreds of ballots were lost in Vancouver, and increased security measures are being implemented.
title: Fires destroy hundreds of ballots in Oregon and Washington drop boxes

description: The Delhi high court ruled that employees are not liable for unpaid taxes deducted by employers but not deposited with the government. The decision stems from a case involving a former Kingfisher Airlines pilot and provides relief for employees facing similar tax demands.
title: Delhi HC backs employees in TDS deposit case

description: In Krishnagiri, a volleyball coach named V Thiyagarajan was arrested for assaulting a student after wrongly accusing her of theft during a tournament. A viral video prompted police investigation, revealing the girl had not stolen the wristwatch but found it on the ground. Thiyagarajan faces legal action and has been remanded in judicial custody.
title: Volleyball coach arrested for assaulting girl student in Tamil Nadu's Krishnagiri

description: Work on a raised pedestrian crossing on Gurgaon’s Golf Course Road has been halted, creating a dangerous unmarked obstruction that has already caused multiple accidents. The stoppage resulted from objections by DLF representatives. The GMDA had begun constructing the crossing to prevent speeding and increase pedestrian safety after several accidents in the area.
title: Flying cars! You won't believe what happened at this Gurgaon speed breaker
